You'll get different results with different phrasing and natural language processing algorithms
But honestly a logo is probably one of the hardest think to ask to an AI. logo are often very abstract and with hidden meaning.
hey, i got some good results already

But I can see how most of those are  "simple"  logos stitched together. 
What I mean is because of the way a neural network work you have to be able to cut the task you're asking the AI into very very very simple problems. Wants picture of a cat ? sure one neuron will check if there's a circle that can ressemble the shape of a cat head, one neuron will check if there's a left ear, one neuron will check if there's a right ear, fur check ? whiskers ? etc
But I'd have no idea how a neural network would work for a logo.
